1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 4=

3
00:01:44,220 --> 00:01:45,220
(Hello!)

4
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,820
(Today,)

5
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:48,488
(I have a very important announcement.)

6
00:01:48,820 --> 00:01:49,700
(Starting today,)

7
00:01:50,180 --> 00:01:52,220
(Shattered Six States
will be paused for a week.)

8
00:01:52,540 --> 00:01:53,180
(Why?)

9
00:01:53,466 --> 00:01:55,180
(Because I want
to support my girlfriend,)

10
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:56,340
(Mimi's new novel.)

11
00:01:56,444 --> 00:01:59,460
(I hope you will give
your attention and time to Mimi.)

12
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:01,500
(Hello, everyone.)

13
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,340
(I'm Mimi.)

14
00:02:02,340 --> 00:02:03,955
(Thank you all for supporting me.)

15
00:02:04,022 --> 00:02:05,688
(And thank you to my dear He Han.)

16
00:02:06,140 --> 00:02:07,820
(He's done so much for me.)

17
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:18,180
Hello?

18
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:21,377
Don't say I'm
not looking out for you, okay?

19
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:22,940
I'll give you one week

20
00:02:22,940 --> 00:02:24,300
to find a better author.

21
00:02:24,940 --> 00:02:25,780
After one week,

22
00:02:25,940 --> 00:02:27,300
I'll resume Shattered Six States.

23
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:29,340
Let's see if anyone can outrun me.

24
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:32,580
Didn't you say you
were pausing for a week

25
00:02:33,060 --> 00:02:35,380
to boost your new girlfriend's rankings?

26
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:38,420
So now, you're doing me a favor instead?

27
00:02:38,420 --> 00:02:40,266
Isn't this getting
two things done at once?

28
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,666
And you should be thanking me.

29
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:44,690
It's like I'm running a 1000-meter race
and you start 100 meters ahead.

30
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,700
I just don't want you to lose too badly.

31
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:50,380
Pausing for a week

32
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:51,780
is nothing to you.

33
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:53,580
If it were Hong Qigong

34
00:02:53,660 --> 00:02:54,340
or Siyuetian,

35
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:56,020
it wouldn't affect them at all.

36
00:02:56,066 --> 00:02:57,244
If you've got the nerve,

37
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:58,700
try pausing for a month.

38
00:02:59,420 --> 00:03:01,060
Let's see if you're still unbeatable.

39
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:08,380
Trying to provoke me, huh?

40
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:09,700
Fine.

41
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:11,355
You've gotten smarter, Lin Zhanqiao.

42
00:03:12,620 --> 00:03:13,380
Good.

43
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:14,740
One month it is.

44
00:03:14,740 --> 00:03:15,540
I'll post it now.

45
00:03:21,940 --> 00:03:23,540
(He Han: Hello, starting today,)

46
00:03:23,540 --> 00:03:25,488
(Shattered Six States
will be paused for a week.)

47
00:03:27,780 --> 00:03:28,580
One month?

48
00:03:40,180 --> 00:03:41,260
Thirty days?

49
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:57,820
One month?

50
00:04:28,220 --> 00:04:32,220
(He Han: Sorry, it will be
paused for one month,)

51
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:34,260
(not one week. Thank you.)

52
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:35,020
One month!

53
00:04:39,466 --> 00:04:41,088
Call all editors
to a meeting immediately.

54
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:41,620
Okay.

55
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:43,377
He Han is pausing for one month.

56
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:44,260
Our authors

57
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:46,060
can go all out to
fight for the top spot.

58
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,820
From one week to one month,

59
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:49,300
has...

60
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,400
Has He Han lost his mind?

61
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:53,500
Whether he has or not,
this is a great opportunity for us.

62
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,460
By tomorrow,

63
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:55,460
we'll see

64
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:58,340
the overall situation
after He Han steps away.

65
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,777
It should be Hong Qigong.

66
00:05:00,380 --> 00:05:02,020
Although her current work is with us,

67
00:05:02,020 --> 00:05:03,540
the rights have already been sold.

68
00:05:03,711 --> 00:05:05,555
At most, we just gain some recognition.

69
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:06,900
If you ask me,

70
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:09,380
this just benefits
Ling Yikai and Zhao Lanxin.

71
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:10,666
You're absolutely right.

72
00:05:12,555 --> 00:05:15,466
Ms. Lin, you have three shortlisted
candidates for the assistant editor.

73
00:05:15,511 --> 00:05:16,700
They'll come in for interviews tomorrow.

74
00:05:16,711 --> 00:05:17,244
Alright.

75
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:20,066
Get everything ready.

76
00:05:20,244 --> 00:05:20,870
- Okay.
- Okay.

77
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:42,980
(Resume, Cai Zhangzhu)

78
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:45,940
Who is it?

79
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:47,740
You're really putting on a show.

80
00:05:48,266 --> 00:05:50,222
Lin Zhanqiao forced you
to stop updating, right?

81
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:52,488
What does this have
to do with Lin Zhanqiao?

82
00:05:52,580 --> 00:05:54,300
I told you, I'm supporting Mimi.

83
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:55,820
She's my girlfriend.

84
00:05:55,820 --> 00:05:57,733
She tells me she loves me
and misses me every day.

85
00:05:57,777 --> 00:05:58,977
I should respond, right?

86
00:05:59,540 --> 00:06:00,660
Am I 20 to you?

87
00:06:01,420 --> 00:06:02,820
You think I'm that easy to fool?

88
00:06:03,066 --> 00:06:05,740
Didn't you see how fast she climbed
the women's rankings today?

89
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,060
Don't give me that.

90
00:06:07,711 --> 00:06:10,400
You're just counting on a hiatus
not being a breach of contract.

91
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:13,511
What did Mr. Fan say?

92
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:14,660
What could he say?

93
00:06:14,866 --> 00:06:16,000
He went crazy, I guess?

94
00:06:16,060 --> 00:06:17,740
Probably thinks I'm scamming him again.

95
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,340
How much did you scam from him this time

96
00:06:21,460 --> 00:06:22,620
that messed him up that badly?

97
00:06:25,955 --> 00:06:26,755
Pretty much.

98
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:28,020
And you left him?

99
00:06:28,740 --> 00:06:29,180
Exactly.

100
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:30,620
What I hate most

101
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:32,180
is his constantly reminding me

102
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:33,700
how much money he's spent on me.

103
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,700
He was reminding you
how much he loved you.

104
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:39,300
What about you?

105
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:40,660
Pausing for a month,

106
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,466
how much do you care about Lin Zhanqiao?

107
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:49,620
Lin Zhanqiao is on her own now,

108
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:51,020
and I had a part in that.

109
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:54,060
Even job changes have
non-compete clauses.

110
00:06:54,740 --> 00:06:55,820
My taking a month off

111
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,460
is just a bit of compensation.

112
00:06:58,460 --> 00:07:00,020
If she can seize this chance,

113
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,580
she can make a comeback.

114
00:07:01,780 --> 00:07:02,580
If she can't,

115
00:07:02,580 --> 00:07:03,860
then that's on her.

116
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:06,460
And it also gives Mimi some exposure.

117
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:08,940
Who wouldn't want
to be a hero to a pretty girl?

118
00:07:08,940 --> 00:07:09,660
Don't you think?

119
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:10,460
Yeah.

120
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:13,380
So what are you giving me
as compensation for this month?

121
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,660
We've got time ahead of us.

122
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:19,700
One month.

123
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,660
Give me the outline for the new novel.

124
00:07:23,460 --> 00:07:24,980
I can at least secure a deposit.

125
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:29,300
A Lotus sports car would work too.

126
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:32,860
The outline it is.

127
00:07:41,340 --> 00:07:41,900
Hong,

128
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:44,260
you've heard about
He Han's hiatus, right?

129
00:07:45,380 --> 00:07:46,380
That's a good thing.

130
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:49,260
I was planning to update today

131
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,780
with some strong plot chapters.

132
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:55,140
Then, tomorrow's top spot
should be yours, Hong.

133
00:07:56,180 --> 00:07:57,500
I hope so.

134
00:07:58,780 --> 00:07:59,730
No one

135
00:07:59,730 --> 00:08:01,660
feels good being under He Han

136
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:02,940
for so long.

137
00:08:03,660 --> 00:08:04,100
Exactly.

138
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:06,220
For the next month,

139
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:07,740
the top spot will probably be yours.

140
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:10,260
I'll do my best.

141
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:11,740
Hong,

142
00:08:12,140 --> 00:08:13,450
on my way here today,

143
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:15,100
I brought you a small gift.

144
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:16,620
Please accept it.

145
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:26,860
In a month,

146
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:29,066
Shattered Six States
might not even be your match.

147
00:08:29,340 --> 00:08:30,900
Looks like we got lucky.

148
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:32,466
We just signed the cooperation intent,

149
00:08:32,511 --> 00:08:33,622
and He Han went on hiatus.

150
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:35,940
At this rate,

151
00:08:36,180 --> 00:08:37,555
our value is about to double.

152
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:40,740
Zhao,

153
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:43,620
if that really happens,

154
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,780
I think we'll need

155
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:47,500
to revisit our contract.

156
00:08:48,620 --> 00:08:49,940
But we already signed it,

157
00:08:50,380 --> 00:08:51,020
Hong.

158
00:08:51,780 --> 00:08:52,460
You...

159
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:53,660
No.

160
00:08:53,980 --> 00:08:54,940
What I mean is,

161
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:56,660
we should add

162
00:08:56,780 --> 00:08:57,940
a supplementary agreement.

163
00:08:59,140 --> 00:08:59,940
After all,

164
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:02,420
things are different now

165
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:04,020
from when we first signed,

166
00:09:04,420 --> 00:09:05,180
right?

167
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:07,980
Of course.

168
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,180
I understand what you mean, Hong.

169
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:17,140
I just came from Hong Qigong.

170
00:09:17,444 --> 00:09:19,755
She's already planning to
raise her price on the spot.

171
00:09:19,820 --> 00:09:21,260
Nothing's even settled yet,

172
00:09:21,377 --> 00:09:23,244
and she's already laying the groundwork.

173
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:25,460
When the tiger's away,
the monkey becomes king.

174
00:09:26,288 --> 00:09:27,980
What happens next is still uncertain,

175
00:09:27,980 --> 00:09:29,140
but for at least a week,

176
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:30,260
she'll be the top name.

177
00:09:30,860 --> 00:09:33,340
Spend more time with her
and keep her steady.

178
00:09:34,377 --> 00:09:35,780
As for how capable she really is

179
00:09:35,911 --> 00:09:37,088
and what she's truly worth,

180
00:09:37,150 --> 00:09:38,222
we'll know after a month,

181
00:09:38,311 --> 00:09:40,330
when He Han returns
and they go head-to-head.

182
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:41,300
Got it.

183
00:10:03,460 --> 00:10:03,820
Ms. Wu.

184
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:05,700
You're here, Ling.

185
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:06,660
Perfect timing.

186
00:10:07,133 --> 00:10:08,680
Chenxing's representative is here too.

187
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:09,740
From Chenxing?

188
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:11,140
Hello.

189
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:12,900
Zhou Mei?

190
00:10:15,022 --> 00:10:16,377
What are you doing here?

191
00:10:18,244 --> 00:10:19,622
The person from Zhiyuan Investment

192
00:10:19,666 --> 00:10:21,340
handling this project is Wu Jian.

193
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,000
(Wu Jian, Zhiyuan China)
Why don't you brief Ms. Wu

194
00:10:25,088 --> 00:10:26,800
on the company's current situation?

195
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:28,660
Of course, if Ms. Wu
is willing to invest,

196
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:30,900
she's already done her research
on Chenxing.

197
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:32,740
But recently,

198
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:35,500
there have been quite
a few changes in the company.

199
00:10:36,260 --> 00:10:37,140
For example,

200
00:10:38,140 --> 00:10:39,660
your sudden resignation, Mr. Ling.

201
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:42,500
So some information hasn't been updated.

202
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:43,740
What information?

203
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:46,100
Go tell Wu Jian

204
00:10:47,060 --> 00:10:47,780
that in order to

205
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:49,260
secure this investment

206
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:50,460
for Ling Yikai's own company,

207
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:51,100
Ling Yikai

208
00:10:51,355 --> 00:10:52,540
hid from her that Chenxing

209
00:10:52,540 --> 00:10:54,420
was about to release a major project.

210
00:10:55,940 --> 00:10:56,660
What project?

211
00:10:57,020 --> 00:10:57,980
You can't tell her yet.

212
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:00,580
Especially not let Ling Yikai find out.

213
00:11:01,380 --> 00:11:02,020
That's fake?

214
00:11:02,660 --> 00:11:03,300
Just stall her.

215
00:11:03,777 --> 00:11:04,800
For half a month.

216
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:06,620
What if she doesn't agree?

217
00:11:06,980 --> 00:11:07,860
Then, one week.

218
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:09,340
If that doesn't work,

219
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,666
even three days would help.

220
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:11,460
Ling,

221
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,380
you left Chenxing
to start your own company

222
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,980
and want to bring this investment over.

223
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:18,780
I can understand that.

224
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:22,900
But if you did it

225
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:26,860
by deliberately withholding
key information from Chenxing,

226
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:28,740
frankly speaking,

227
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,422
that's a matter of professional ethics.

228
00:11:30,555 --> 00:11:32,333
Ms. Wu, that's a serious accusation.

229
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,340
I can assure you that before I left,

230
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:35,420
everything at Chenxing

231
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:37,220
was fully transparent to you.

232
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:38,380
A secret weapon?

233
00:11:38,780 --> 00:11:39,688
What secret weapon?

234
00:11:40,820 --> 00:11:42,940
If Chenxing didn't
have a new trump card,

235
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:44,700
why would they let He Han go

236
00:11:44,733 --> 00:11:45,730
and lose Hong Qigong too?

237
00:11:45,730 --> 00:11:46,660
What trump card?

238
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:48,222
If there were one, would I have left?

239
00:11:48,420 --> 00:11:50,180
I left because things
were going downhill.

240
00:11:50,644 --> 00:11:51,940
Zhou Mei, you need to be clear.

241
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:54,088
This so-called trump card,
in terms of commercial value,

242
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,790
can it compete
with He Han or Hong Qigong?

243
00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:57,820
Why would I tell you?

244
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:00,060
So you can start poking around again

245
00:12:00,060 --> 00:12:00,820
like a weasel?

246
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:02,140
So there is no trump card.

247
00:12:03,580 --> 00:12:03,980
Ms. Wu,

248
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:06,140
Zhou Mei isn't even from Chenxing.

249
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:07,140
She's from a PR firm,

250
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:08,720
specializing in stirring things up.

251
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:10,210
If we're talking
about stirring things up,

252
00:12:10,222 --> 00:12:11,659
who does it better than you, Mr. Ling?

253
00:12:11,660 --> 00:12:12,300
How about this?

254
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:15,740
I...

255
00:12:16,580 --> 00:12:17,740
won't rush into a decision.

256
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:19,140
I'll observe for another week.

257
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:22,140
Ms. Zhou says Chenxing
is about to make a move,

258
00:12:22,940 --> 00:12:23,820
so I'll wait and see.

259
00:12:24,740 --> 00:12:25,780
If nothing happens,

260
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:27,700
I'll still lean toward
working with Ling.

261
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:30,380
Let's go by results, shall we?

262
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:32,140
No problem.

263
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:36,460
Zhou Mei,

264
00:12:37,620 --> 00:12:38,420
make yourself clear.

265
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,022
What exactly is this "secret weapon"?

266
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:42,660
Do you know why I dumped you back then?

267
00:12:47,644 --> 00:12:49,180
If Chenxing had any kind of trump card,

268
00:12:49,180 --> 00:12:50,100
how could I not know?

269
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:53,820
It's because the way
you go about things is just too ugly.

270
00:12:54,260 --> 00:12:55,260
Too ugly?

271
00:12:55,260 --> 00:12:56,060
Let me ask you,

272
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:57,900
can being "proper"

273
00:12:58,555 --> 00:13:00,311
bring in tens of millions in investment?

274
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:02,700
No. But it can earn you
a woman's respect.

275
00:13:02,710 --> 00:13:04,610
Once I have money,
women will respect me anyway.

276
00:13:04,620 --> 00:13:06,244
That depends on what kind of women.

277
00:13:09,140 --> 00:13:10,460
So, there is no secret weapon.

278
00:13:13,260 --> 00:13:14,620
You can lie to women,

279
00:13:14,780 --> 00:13:16,020
and women can lie to you too.

280
00:13:16,511 --> 00:13:18,688
Intelligence has nothing
to do with gender.

281
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:32,500
(Food compatibility and restrictions)

282
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:32,860
Mom,

283
00:13:33,355 --> 00:13:34,340
there are only two of us.

284
00:13:34,340 --> 00:13:35,420
We can't finish all this.

285
00:13:36,620 --> 00:13:37,740
If you can't, take it home,

286
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:39,020
or I'll eat it tomorrow.

287
00:13:39,244 --> 00:13:40,700
You rarely have time to come over,

288
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:42,300
so of course, I made more dishes.

289
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:45,180
Dad's birthday

290
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:46,777
is still more than a week away,

291
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:48,340
and you're preparing now?

292
00:13:48,580 --> 00:13:49,644
Isn't that a bit early?

293
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:52,340
It's normal to plan ahead.

294
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:53,980
I've already told him

295
00:13:54,044 --> 00:13:56,133
that the three of us will
have dinner together.

296
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:58,060
I'll bring the dishes
over the day before

297
00:13:58,060 --> 00:13:59,340
and help him clean up.

298
00:13:59,511 --> 00:14:00,780
The next day we'll have a meal,

299
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:02,020
tidy everything up,

300
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:03,222
and then I'll leave.

301
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:04,740
And he still wouldn't agree.

302
00:14:05,340 --> 00:14:06,660
Why don't we just eat out?

303
00:14:07,511 --> 00:14:09,133
I can book a restaurant for you.

304
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,000
So you don't have
to go through the trouble.

305
00:14:11,020 --> 00:14:11,940
I'll talk to him again.

306
00:14:12,180 --> 00:14:13,260
Maybe he'll agree.

307
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,380
Eating out

308
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:15,860
is expensive and not hygienic.

309
00:14:16,020 --> 00:14:17,700
How can it compare to home cooking?

310
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:19,860
I can make extra food, bring it over,

311
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:20,860
and put it in his fridge,

312
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:22,700
so he can eat it for a few more days.

313
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:24,860
How about this?

314
00:14:25,340 --> 00:14:25,980
Tell him

315
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:27,940
I won't go over a day early.

316
00:14:28,940 --> 00:14:30,900
I'll just bring the food in the morning.

317
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:34,022
You don't need to give me more,
I'm already...

318
00:14:34,060 --> 00:14:35,140
Already full.

319
00:14:38,540 --> 00:14:41,220
Dad just doesn't want you
to go over to see him.

320
00:14:41,660 --> 00:14:42,900
So, why insist on going?

321
00:14:43,740 --> 00:14:44,660
Out of the whole year,

322
00:14:44,820 --> 00:14:45,580
on his birthday,

323
00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:47,540
can't the three of us be together?

324
00:14:48,460 --> 00:14:50,340
But gathering
at a restaurant is the same.

325
00:14:50,340 --> 00:14:51,380
There's no difference.

326
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:53,980
What family are we?

327
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,340
Out of 365 days,

328
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:58,020
for 364 days,

329
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,660
he wants his freedom

330
00:14:59,660 --> 00:15:01,020
and his own space.

331
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:02,340
And I've given it to him.

332
00:15:02,580 --> 00:15:03,700
Just one day a year.

333
00:15:04,020 --> 00:15:05,820
Can't we celebrate like other families?

334
00:15:06,820 --> 00:15:08,380
I'm not asking for much.

335
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:11,020
We're both already in our sixties.

336
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:12,980
One day a year.

337
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:15,420
Even if we both live to 90 years old,

338
00:15:15,860 --> 00:15:17,911
that's only
a little over 20 days in total.

339
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:20,620
I've let him go in this life.

340
00:15:21,460 --> 00:15:23,100
Next life,
I don't want to see him again.

341
00:15:25,060 --> 00:15:27,540
Take the packed food to your dad later.

342
00:15:36,420 --> 00:15:37,740
Bring the food with you.

343
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:42,140
They're all your favorites.

344
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:44,540
I told you,
I don't need you to bring me food.

345
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:45,660
I can take care of myself.

346
00:15:46,444 --> 00:15:47,888
But you still brought all this.

347
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:49,644
Either you take it back,

348
00:15:50,244 --> 00:15:51,511
or I'll throw it away.

349
00:15:52,780 --> 00:15:54,540
And don't bring up the birthday again.

350
00:15:55,620 --> 00:15:56,780
I agreed to eat out.

351
00:15:56,844 --> 00:15:58,266
Coming here is not an option.

352
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:00,620
Go back and tell your mom

353
00:16:01,540 --> 00:16:02,580
everything is fine here.

354
00:16:02,940 --> 00:16:04,940
I don't want her
coming over and disturbing me.

355
00:16:13,140 --> 00:16:14,888
These are all your dad's favorites.

356
00:16:15,340 --> 00:16:17,140
My mom asked me to bring them to him.

357
00:16:18,044 --> 00:16:19,933
You've been to your dad's place too?

358
00:16:24,620 --> 00:16:25,940
When I left just now,

359
00:16:25,940 --> 00:16:27,066
he walked me downstairs.

360
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:29,220
Six floors.

361
00:16:29,311 --> 00:16:30,820
Going up and down once like that

362
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:32,133
is already exhausting for him.

363
00:16:32,511 --> 00:16:33,400
But even so,

364
00:16:33,660 --> 00:16:35,180
he'd rather live there alone

365
00:16:35,488 --> 00:16:38,177
than stay with my mom in
an apartment with an elevator.

366
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:40,020
No one else around.

367
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:41,140
No arguments.

368
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,755
No divorce either.

369
00:16:43,020 --> 00:16:44,220
They just drag it out like this

370
00:16:44,866 --> 00:16:46,022
for a lifetime.

371
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:50,580
So,

372
00:16:50,940 --> 00:16:52,900
if you had to choose between
my mom and your mom,

373
00:16:52,955 --> 00:16:54,244
who would you pick?

374
00:16:55,020 --> 00:16:55,580
My dad.

375
00:16:59,380 --> 00:17:00,177
By the way,

376
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:03,500
I read Hong Qigong's update today,

377
00:17:03,660 --> 00:17:04,860
so did she deliberately

378
00:17:04,860 --> 00:17:05,980
push such intense plot points

379
00:17:06,288 --> 00:17:07,688
to fight for the top spot?

380
00:17:07,820 --> 00:17:09,060
She revised it herself.

381
00:17:09,180 --> 00:17:11,288
You have to go all
in at a time like this, right?

382
00:17:11,660 --> 00:17:12,980
With He Han on hiatus,

383
00:17:13,111 --> 00:17:14,533
she'll be number one tomorrow?

384
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:17,020
Unless a dark horse shows up,

385
00:17:22,540 --> 00:17:23,100
probably.

386
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,755
You've been going
to Qingpu a lot lately?

387
00:17:29,420 --> 00:17:30,355
How do you know?

388
00:17:30,460 --> 00:17:32,911
I've seen you buy coffee
from this place several times.

389
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:34,660
Meeting a friend.

390
00:17:38,780 --> 00:17:40,140
(Reincarnation of Ten Thousand Bones)

391
00:17:40,140 --> 00:17:42,020
(Please select your tip amount.)

392
00:17:42,020 --> 00:17:43,340
For Hong Qigong's update today...

393
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:45,820
you only tipped five?

394
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:47,020
That stingy?

395
00:17:47,540 --> 00:17:48,700
That's all it's worth.

396
00:17:49,020 --> 00:17:49,660
What about mine?

397
00:17:49,977 --> 00:17:51,822
Even if you paid me, I wouldn't read it.

398
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:57,260
Why are you always like this with me?

399
00:17:57,540 --> 00:17:58,460
I've been supportive.

400
00:17:58,460 --> 00:18:00,060
I even paused for a month for you.

401
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:02,260
Can't you at least encourage me?

402
00:18:02,355 --> 00:18:03,860
I've really put effort
into writing this.

403
00:18:03,860 --> 00:18:05,260
You're amazing. It's the best.

404
00:18:05,260 --> 00:18:07,020
You're just brushing me off.

405
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:09,460
- We'll talk tomorrow.
- He Han.

406
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:10,830
- I'll sleep.
- Why are you always like this with me?

407
00:18:10,844 --> 00:18:13,022
You should head back early.
Get some rest.

408
00:18:15,288 --> 00:18:17,333
Why don't you
ever let me into your bedroom?

409
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:18,822
I'm not used to it.

410
00:18:18,980 --> 00:18:20,180
When will you get used to it?

411
00:18:20,340 --> 00:18:21,260
Never.

412
00:18:22,844 --> 00:18:24,866
You've got another
girlfriend hidden in there?

413
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:25,977
More than one, actually.

414
00:18:27,140 --> 00:18:28,540
Why can Dai Shan go in, then?

415
00:18:29,820 --> 00:18:30,940
Because she's never cared

416
00:18:30,940 --> 00:18:32,800
whether there's another woman inside.

417
00:18:33,180 --> 00:18:33,955
Good night.

418
00:19:02,580 --> 00:19:02,980
Here.

419
00:19:05,860 --> 00:19:06,700
Still up this late?

420
00:19:07,140 --> 00:19:08,000
Because of He Han?

421
00:19:10,180 --> 00:19:11,340
The changes at work

422
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:13,220
all started because of him.

423
00:19:14,888 --> 00:19:16,888
He stopped updating
because of you, didn't he?

424
00:19:18,340 --> 00:19:20,140
He said it was for Mimi.

425
00:19:22,060 --> 00:19:22,933
From what I see,

426
00:19:23,140 --> 00:19:24,700
he was clearing the way for you

427
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:28,700
to give you time to sign a new author

428
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,577
and a chance to get back on your feet.

429
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:32,740
Otherwise, if you really collapsed,

430
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:34,060
he'd feel bad about it.

431
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:37,300
But his pride is great,

432
00:19:37,755 --> 00:19:39,140
so he wouldn't say it outright.

433
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,000
Did I get that right?

434
00:19:44,580 --> 00:19:45,220
I don't know.

435
00:19:46,740 --> 00:19:47,780
I don't read minds,

436
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,444
and I don't want to spend energy

437
00:19:51,660 --> 00:19:53,540
trying to figure him out.

438
00:19:55,244 --> 00:19:57,311
The two of you are just being stubborn.

439
00:19:58,180 --> 00:20:00,500
Deep down, neither of you
wants the other to suffer.

440
00:20:02,380 --> 00:20:04,500
Your company is just across
the street from his hotel.

441
00:20:04,622 --> 00:20:06,030
All it takes is one
of you crossing over,

442
00:20:06,044 --> 00:20:07,911
and everything would
go back to how it was.

443
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:16,740
Two highways.

444
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:19,100
On a navigation map,

445
00:20:20,020 --> 00:20:20,900
they overlap.

446
00:20:21,222 --> 00:20:22,933
They look like they're together.

447
00:20:23,711 --> 00:20:25,511
But in reality,
not only do those two roads

448
00:20:26,100 --> 00:20:28,260
have distance between them,

449
00:20:28,688 --> 00:20:30,866
but they also lead
to different destinations.

450
00:20:34,460 --> 00:20:35,500
In this world,

451
00:20:36,980 --> 00:20:37,780
how can two people

452
00:20:37,780 --> 00:20:39,540
be heading toward the exact same place?

453
00:20:42,620 --> 00:20:43,740
Isn't it just about

454
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:45,660
walking together

455
00:20:45,755 --> 00:20:46,980
for as long as you can?

456
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:11,377
Morning.

457
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:11,980
Have you heard?

458
00:21:11,980 --> 00:21:12,690
Morning, Ms. Lin.

459
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:13,740
No.

460
00:21:14,460 --> 00:21:15,580
That rose pretty fast.

461
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:17,180
So? Hong Qigong took first place?

462
00:21:17,260 --> 00:21:17,860
No.

463
00:21:18,260 --> 00:21:18,900
Then, who?

464
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:30,500
Watch your step.

465
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:31,180
Alright.

466
00:21:33,380 --> 00:21:33,700
Okay.

467
00:21:34,340 --> 00:21:34,740
Careful.

468
00:21:34,740 --> 00:21:35,180
Ms. Hong,

469
00:21:35,820 --> 00:21:36,970
I'm leaving.

470
00:21:36,970 --> 00:21:37,300
Alright.

471
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:38,220
Okay.

472
00:21:38,300 --> 00:21:38,820
I'm off.

473
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:39,620
Come again.

474
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:40,260
Take care.

475
00:21:40,660 --> 00:21:41,300
Here.

476
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:42,060
Careful.

477
00:21:56,020 --> 00:21:56,420
Hello?

478
00:21:57,420 --> 00:21:58,180
Hong,

479
00:21:58,900 --> 00:21:59,900
we miscalculated.

480
00:22:00,540 --> 00:22:01,060
Gu Yan?

481
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:02,540
Who is Gu Yan?

482
00:22:02,711 --> 00:22:04,688
(Daily Ranking: Drunk Old Friend)
New author?

483
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,260
Who is Gu Yan?

484
00:22:06,780 --> 00:22:07,820
Never even heard of him.

485
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,100
But he's climbing fast.

486
00:22:12,660 --> 00:22:15,340
(Ranking, Drunk Old Friend,
Reincarnation of Ten Thousand Bones)

487
00:22:18,711 --> 00:22:20,100
I read until four in the morning.

488
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:22,450
It's incredible.
Never seen writing this good.

489
00:22:22,450 --> 00:22:23,620
The style is sharp.

490
00:22:23,620 --> 00:22:24,460
Indeed.

491
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:25,860
Hello.

492
00:22:25,911 --> 00:22:28,044
Boss probably threw up blood
on the way here.

493
00:22:28,060 --> 00:22:28,990
How far did you guys get?

494
00:22:29,111 --> 00:22:30,219
Caught up in one night. You?

495
00:22:30,220 --> 00:22:30,660
Same.

496
00:22:31,044 --> 00:22:32,060
We were just discussing it.

497
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:33,940
Feels like a veteran in disguise.

498
00:22:34,340 --> 00:22:35,260
Could it be He Han?

499
00:22:35,311 --> 00:22:37,220
Otherwise, how could
the timing be this perfect?

500
00:22:37,288 --> 00:22:38,720
Didn't he say he's on
a one-month hiatus?

501
00:22:38,730 --> 00:22:40,555
Maybe he's using a new pen name
to test the waters.

502
00:22:40,666 --> 00:22:41,377
No way.

503
00:22:41,644 --> 00:22:43,422
An author's style always shows through,

504
00:22:43,488 --> 00:22:45,177
no matter how you try to hide it.

505
00:22:45,180 --> 00:22:46,160
Doesn't read like He Han.

506
00:22:46,180 --> 00:22:46,700
A newcomer?

507
00:22:47,044 --> 00:22:48,022
Doesn't feel like one.

508
00:22:48,380 --> 00:22:49,340
If it's not He Han,

509
00:22:49,340 --> 00:22:50,060
this person

510
00:22:50,060 --> 00:22:51,700
will be his biggest rival.

511
00:22:51,780 --> 00:22:52,340
Definitely.

512
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:10,220
You're really calm
enough to still sleep?

513
00:23:12,580 --> 00:23:13,500
Sleep, my foot.

514
00:23:13,860 --> 00:23:16,300
Over 20 messages
and ten calls this morning.

515
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:18,000
Everyone is asking me who Gu Yan is.

516
00:23:18,020 --> 00:23:19,300
How would I know who Gu Yan is?

517
00:23:22,660 --> 00:23:23,900
Well, now you know?

518
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:28,860
Anyway, it's not someone I recognize.

519
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:31,450
I called Dingqi to check.

520
00:23:31,450 --> 00:23:32,220
A new author.

521
00:23:35,020 --> 00:23:35,888
Whose new author?

522
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:37,660
Lin Zhanqiao's.

523
00:23:40,140 --> 00:23:40,900
Never heard of him.

524
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,620
I'm worried that after a month,

525
00:23:43,620 --> 00:23:44,980
people will only know Gu Yan

526
00:23:44,980 --> 00:23:46,500
and forget who He Han is.

527
00:23:48,740 --> 00:23:50,860
If he really is
Lin Zhanqiao's secret weapon,

528
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:52,700
then your "goodwill move"

529
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:53,860
might cost you

530
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:56,340
your future position.

531
00:23:57,540 --> 00:23:59,100
If he's not Lin Zhanqiao's,

532
00:23:59,660 --> 00:24:01,060
if Gu Yan stays in first place

533
00:24:01,260 --> 00:24:04,020
for just one week,

534
00:24:04,860 --> 00:24:06,940
he will not only become a threat to you,

535
00:24:07,111 --> 00:24:08,688
but also make the future path

536
00:24:08,711 --> 00:24:11,100
for Lin Zhanqiao and Chenxing
increasingly difficult.

537
00:24:11,100 --> 00:24:12,940
And your "goodwill move"

538
00:24:13,511 --> 00:24:14,977
becomes setting them up for a fall.

539
00:24:16,740 --> 00:24:17,860
It's only been one day.

540
00:24:17,940 --> 00:24:19,180
Let it play out a bit.

541
00:24:20,580 --> 00:24:22,420
The moment Gu Yan showed up,

542
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:24,300
he dropped 20 chapters.

543
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:26,980
That's no lucky break.

544
00:24:27,180 --> 00:24:29,140
He came prepared.

545
00:24:29,980 --> 00:24:31,780
I can't just announce a hiatus yesterday

546
00:24:31,780 --> 00:24:33,355
and take it back today, right?

547
00:24:33,555 --> 00:24:35,622
Besides, having a rival
makes things more interesting.

548
00:24:38,860 --> 00:24:39,860
As far as I know,

549
00:24:39,860 --> 00:24:42,620
when Zhao Lanxin and
Ling Yikai left Chenxing,

550
00:24:42,780 --> 00:24:44,780
they had already signed
a few young authors.

551
00:24:47,580 --> 00:24:49,300
If Gu Yan is one of Zhao Lanxin's,

552
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:51,222
then the one
who should be worried isn't me.

553
00:24:51,266 --> 00:24:52,044
It's Hong Qigong.

554
00:24:52,260 --> 00:24:53,700
She just signed with a new company,

555
00:24:53,733 --> 00:24:56,000
and she's already destined
to be second place again.

556
00:24:56,540 --> 00:25:02,380
(Hong Qigong)

557
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:19,820
Hello, Ms. Hong.

558
00:25:20,340 --> 00:25:20,740
Hello,

559
00:25:21,060 --> 00:25:21,820
Zhanqiao,

560
00:25:22,180 --> 00:25:24,260
what's the background of this Gu Yan?

561
00:25:25,180 --> 00:25:27,180
Is he one of Zhao Lanxin's new authors?

562
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:30,100
I can update a few more chapters today.

563
00:25:30,900 --> 00:25:32,140
Get me a homepage feature,

564
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:34,140
and I'll turn things around tomorrow.

565
00:25:34,420 --> 00:25:34,980
Ms. Hong,

566
00:25:36,020 --> 00:25:38,900
first, Zhao Lanxin and I are
no longer with the same company.

567
00:25:39,140 --> 00:25:41,220
You and Zhao Lanxin
are now on the same side.

568
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:42,740
I'm not familiar

569
00:25:42,740 --> 00:25:44,222
with your company's content.

570
00:25:44,620 --> 00:25:45,020
Second,

571
00:25:45,340 --> 00:25:46,820
if you want to release more chapters,

572
00:25:46,820 --> 00:25:47,540
that's fine.

573
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:49,380
But I don't have the authority

574
00:25:49,466 --> 00:25:50,933
to give you homepage placement.

575
00:25:50,980 --> 00:25:53,660
But I'm still a Chenxing author.

576
00:25:54,100 --> 00:25:56,100
Our contract hasn't expired.

577
00:25:56,340 --> 00:25:57,540
We have an agreement.

578
00:25:58,266 --> 00:25:59,530
According to the contract,

579
00:25:59,530 --> 00:26:01,740
you're free not to renew
with us after it ends.

580
00:26:02,460 --> 00:26:04,140
You can sign with Zhao Lanxin's company.

581
00:26:04,244 --> 00:26:05,600
And according to the contract,

582
00:26:05,688 --> 00:26:07,711
I'm not obligated to give
you homepage resources.

583
00:26:09,140 --> 00:26:11,940
I haven't signed with Zhao Lanxin yet.

584
00:26:12,380 --> 00:26:13,940
There's still room for negotiation

585
00:26:14,260 --> 00:26:15,380
on renewing with you.

586
00:26:15,820 --> 00:26:17,100
I'll pass, Ms. Hong.

587
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:18,860
An editor will contact you later.

588
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:19,980
We'll see,

589
00:26:19,980 --> 00:26:21,660
given the current situation,

590
00:26:21,660 --> 00:26:23,180
what adjustments can be made

591
00:26:23,420 --> 00:26:25,420
to improve performance.

592
00:26:26,700 --> 00:26:27,420
That's it for now.

593
00:26:27,860 --> 00:26:28,660
Goodbye, Ms. Hong.

594
00:26:33,940 --> 00:26:35,860
Hong Qigong must have been sidelined

595
00:26:35,860 --> 00:26:36,860
on Zhao Lanxin's side.

596
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:38,266
That's why she came back to us.

597
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:40,220
As for this Gu Yan,

598
00:26:40,660 --> 00:26:42,740
if he's one of the young authors

599
00:26:42,740 --> 00:26:45,140
Zhao Lanxin signed recently,

600
00:26:45,620 --> 00:26:47,660
Hong Qigong's contract with Zhao Lanxin

601
00:26:47,780 --> 00:26:49,140
probably won't go through.

602
00:26:50,180 --> 00:26:51,100
As for Hong Qigong,

603
00:26:51,177 --> 00:26:53,288
just focus on discussing
content with her,

604
00:26:53,340 --> 00:26:54,900
editing, and her update schedule.

605
00:26:54,910 --> 00:26:56,380
Don't talk to her about anything else.

606
00:26:56,380 --> 00:26:57,380
Push everything to me.

607
00:26:57,740 --> 00:26:58,180
Understood.

608
00:26:59,180 --> 00:26:59,580
Ms. Lin,

609
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:01,620
may I say something?

610
00:27:02,380 --> 00:27:04,420
If we renew with Hong Qigong,

611
00:27:04,420 --> 00:27:05,620
the situation going forward

612
00:27:05,711 --> 00:27:07,422
will actually be quite favorable for us.

613
00:27:11,180 --> 00:27:11,980
As for Hong Qigong,

614
00:27:12,780 --> 00:27:13,940
just part on good terms.

615
00:27:16,060 --> 00:27:16,460
Alright.

616
00:27:34,577 --> 00:27:35,780
Right now, everyone outside thinks

617
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:37,266
Gu Yan is our newly signed author.

618
00:27:37,311 --> 00:27:39,133
Have you found out
which company he's with?

619
00:27:39,260 --> 00:27:39,740
Not yet.

620
00:27:40,340 --> 00:27:42,220
Dingqi only gave me his email.

621
00:27:42,780 --> 00:27:45,020
They said they couldn't share
his WeChat or phone number.

622
00:27:45,311 --> 00:27:46,460
I've already sent an email.

623
00:27:46,777 --> 00:27:47,822
What about Weibo DMs?

624
00:27:47,933 --> 00:27:48,933
He doesn't have Weibo.

625
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:50,580
No other social media either.

626
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:54,511
Not even answering the investor's call?

627
00:27:55,660 --> 00:27:56,940
She must be asking about Gu Yan.

628
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:01,177
If Lin Zhanqiao can
suddenly pull out a trump card,

629
00:28:01,460 --> 00:28:02,420
why can't we?

630
00:28:06,380 --> 00:28:07,333
Hello, Ms. Wu.

631
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:09,100
Yes.

632
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:12,180
Everyone's talking about
Gu Yan this morning.

633
00:28:14,980 --> 00:28:15,540
Don't worry.

634
00:28:15,780 --> 00:28:17,666
We've already started
reaching out to him.

635
00:28:18,340 --> 00:28:19,980
Given his current momentum,

636
00:28:20,140 --> 00:28:21,380
his price is indeed high.

637
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:22,820
But rest assured,

638
00:28:22,820 --> 00:28:24,020
if we can sign him,

639
00:28:24,711 --> 00:28:26,688
no matter what Chenxing's trump card is,

640
00:28:26,980 --> 00:28:28,140
it won't matter.

641
00:28:31,860 --> 00:28:32,755
Understood.

642
00:28:35,300 --> 00:28:37,100
If that's the case,

643
00:28:37,580 --> 00:28:38,220
I think...

644
00:28:40,180 --> 00:28:40,620
Three days.

645
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,300
Three days to sign Gu Yan.

646
00:28:44,900 --> 00:28:45,260
Alright.

647
00:28:47,380 --> 00:28:48,220
Three days?

648
00:28:48,460 --> 00:28:49,100
Are you crazy?

649
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:50,940
You don't even know where he is.

650
00:28:50,940 --> 00:28:52,260
Ms. Wu said we have to sign Gu Yan

651
00:28:52,260 --> 00:28:52,980
at all costs.

652
00:28:53,420 --> 00:28:55,180
It'll raise our rating with Zhiyuan.

653
00:28:55,260 --> 00:28:56,066
In this round,

654
00:28:56,222 --> 00:28:58,066
they'll increase
the investment by 50 percent.

655
00:29:00,620 --> 00:29:02,420
But Gu Yan isn't
someone you can just sign

656
00:29:02,420 --> 00:29:04,180
because you want to.

657
00:29:04,311 --> 00:29:06,555
We still have the new author
planning meeting this afternoon.

658
00:29:06,660 --> 00:29:08,955
Developing new authors takes a lot
of effort with uncertain returns.

659
00:29:09,022 --> 00:29:11,100
We can't afford that gamble right now.
We might end up with nothing.

660
00:29:11,180 --> 00:29:13,244
Gu Yan is different.
His value is already proven.

661
00:29:13,333 --> 00:29:15,060
What if he's already
signed with someone else?

662
00:29:15,060 --> 00:29:16,111
Then we take him anyway.

663
00:29:16,660 --> 00:29:17,580
We'll cover the penalty.

664
00:29:19,260 --> 00:29:19,700
But...

665
00:29:20,380 --> 00:29:21,660
Zhao Lanxin will find a way

666
00:29:22,420 --> 00:29:23,660
to get anything she wants.

667
00:29:25,060 --> 00:29:25,980
You said that yourself.

668
00:29:27,420 --> 00:29:28,180
And that's exactly

669
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:30,200
why I chose you.

670
00:29:44,666 --> 00:29:46,022
Wait for my good news.

671
00:29:46,860 --> 00:29:47,540
Hello, Mom.

672
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:49,500
I'm really busy tonight.

673
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:50,700
I'll be tied up very late.

674
00:29:51,266 --> 00:29:52,660
I'll come see you tomorrow, okay?

675
00:29:52,660 --> 00:29:53,900
Just don't come over today.

676
00:29:55,660 --> 00:29:56,060
That's it.

677
00:29:57,577 --> 00:30:00,020
Ms. Lin, the new assistant has arrived.
Please take a look.

678
00:30:00,020 --> 00:30:02,140
If everything's fine, we'll sign
the contract this afternoon.

679
00:30:02,140 --> 00:30:03,180
This is her office.

680
00:30:04,020 --> 00:30:04,540
Mr. He.

681
00:30:05,140 --> 00:30:05,700
Lin Zhanqiao.

682
00:30:06,100 --> 00:30:06,650
Cai Zhangzhu.

683
00:30:06,650 --> 00:30:07,060
Hello.

684
00:30:08,340 --> 00:30:09,060
New girlfriend?

685
00:30:09,780 --> 00:30:10,900
We just met in the elevator.

686
00:30:13,900 --> 00:30:14,300
Ms. Lin,

687
00:30:14,900 --> 00:30:16,500
Cai Zhangzhu, your new assistant.

688
00:30:16,780 --> 00:30:18,180
Lin Zhanqiao, your new boss.

689
00:30:19,380 --> 00:30:20,980
Hello, Ms. Lin. I'm Cai Zhangzhu.

690
00:30:21,340 --> 00:30:23,380
I'm really excited to
start working at Chenxing.

691
00:30:27,820 --> 00:30:29,660
And I'm a huge fan of Mr. He Han.

692
00:30:31,660 --> 00:30:32,580
I really...

693
00:30:32,700 --> 00:30:33,900
I practically have

694
00:30:34,020 --> 00:30:35,460
all the iconic scenes memorized.

695
00:30:35,620 --> 00:30:36,820
And I honestly never imagined

696
00:30:36,888 --> 00:30:38,244
that on my first day at Chenxing,

697
00:30:38,250 --> 00:30:39,911
I'd run into my idol in the elevator.

698
00:30:43,140 --> 00:30:43,620
Oh, right,

699
00:30:43,688 --> 00:30:46,000
I even drew some
of the characters from the book.

700
00:30:46,980 --> 00:30:47,820
Let me show you.

701
00:30:47,820 --> 00:30:49,066
You don't need to show me.

702
00:30:49,844 --> 00:30:50,740
Let me take a look.

703
00:30:53,140 --> 00:30:53,700
Not bad.

704
00:30:54,700 --> 00:30:55,580
"Qingqiu Qiluo Hand."

705
00:30:56,980 --> 00:30:58,140
Not bad at all.

706
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:01,333
It's Lin Erniang who walks
without touching the ground.

707
00:31:01,555 --> 00:31:03,780
Let me tell you, this character
was based on your boss.

708
00:31:03,780 --> 00:31:04,220
Right?

709
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:06,500
But you didn't quite
capture her essence.

710
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:08,300
I'll explain it to you later.

711
00:31:11,220 --> 00:31:11,740
Miss Cai,

712
00:31:12,980 --> 00:31:14,911
if you came to Chenxing
to chase a celebrity,

713
00:31:15,020 --> 00:31:15,980
then let me be clear.

714
00:31:16,620 --> 00:31:17,580
He Han and Chenxing

715
00:31:17,660 --> 00:31:19,422
no longer have any working relationship.

716
00:31:21,740 --> 00:31:23,660
But you're friends, aren't you?

717
00:31:23,820 --> 00:31:24,180
Yes.

718
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:24,780
No.

719
00:31:27,860 --> 00:31:28,980
I've reviewed your resume.

720
00:31:29,777 --> 00:31:31,866
Three years abroad studying
business management.

721
00:31:32,022 --> 00:31:33,222
Strong academic background.

722
00:31:33,580 --> 00:31:36,100
But it doesn't suit
our current assistant editor position.

723
00:31:37,060 --> 00:31:38,140
Work is for yourself,

724
00:31:38,380 --> 00:31:39,300
not for idol-chasing.

725
00:31:40,180 --> 00:31:41,700
You can find something more suitable.

726
00:31:47,780 --> 00:31:48,220
Ms. Lin,

727
00:31:48,620 --> 00:31:49,660
I love reading novels,

728
00:31:49,660 --> 00:31:50,860
especially Chinese fiction.

729
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:53,420
I believe my background
in economics and management

730
00:31:53,420 --> 00:31:56,420
can help support your work.

731
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:58,466
And being familiar with Chinese novels

732
00:31:58,555 --> 00:32:02,060
fits well with Chenxing's business.

733
00:32:02,620 --> 00:32:04,580
Also, when I was in the UK,

734
00:32:04,580 --> 00:32:05,533
I interned at a magazine

735
00:32:05,577 --> 00:32:07,666
and worked as an assistant
to the publisher.

736
00:32:11,260 --> 00:32:11,860
How about this?

737
00:32:13,500 --> 00:32:14,540
If you don't mind,

738
00:32:14,660 --> 00:32:15,911
you can come work with me.

739
00:32:16,580 --> 00:32:17,500
My girlfriend, Mimi,

740
00:32:17,620 --> 00:32:19,100
happens to need an editor right now.

741
00:32:19,177 --> 00:32:20,140
Have you read her novel,

742
00:32:20,140 --> 00:32:21,244
Love-Obsessed Husband?

743
00:32:22,460 --> 00:32:23,020
Not yet.

744
00:32:23,460 --> 00:32:24,180
It's really good.

745
00:32:24,940 --> 00:32:26,340
If I could work

746
00:32:26,340 --> 00:32:27,140
with you,

747
00:32:27,311 --> 00:32:27,940
I... I really...

748
00:32:28,020 --> 00:32:29,140
I'd do anything.

749
00:32:29,300 --> 00:32:30,100
That would be great.

750
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,860
But I'm on a one-month hiatus right now.

751
00:32:31,911 --> 00:32:32,980
You can help Mimi first.

752
00:32:32,980 --> 00:32:34,660
When I resume,
you can come work with me. OK?

753
00:32:35,380 --> 00:32:35,820
Okay.

754
00:32:36,020 --> 00:32:37,020
That's great. Let's go.

755
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:38,088
Give me five minutes.

756
00:32:38,090 --> 00:32:38,740
Goodbye, Ms. Lin.

757
00:32:38,740 --> 00:32:40,420
I live across from the hotel.
I didn't know...

758
00:32:40,444 --> 00:32:41,133
Wait.

759
00:32:43,060 --> 00:32:43,660
Miss Cai,

760
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:46,260
personally,

761
00:32:46,740 --> 00:32:48,511
I think Chenxing
can help you grow faster

762
00:32:48,740 --> 00:32:50,260
and learn more.

763
00:32:51,088 --> 00:32:52,488
We have a large pool of authors

764
00:32:52,533 --> 00:32:53,890
and a well-structured editorial team.

765
00:32:53,900 --> 00:32:55,780
As someone new to the industry,

766
00:32:55,780 --> 00:32:57,466
you'll be able to see
the bigger picture.

767
00:32:58,700 --> 00:32:59,820
Then, Mr. He Han...

768
00:33:00,700 --> 00:33:01,940
Of course, you can first read

769
00:33:01,940 --> 00:33:03,088
Love-Obsessed Husband

770
00:33:03,177 --> 00:33:05,222
and decide whether
you want to work with him

771
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:06,740
and his girlfriend

772
00:33:07,460 --> 00:33:08,540
as their assistant editor.

773
00:33:09,860 --> 00:33:11,140
After a month,

774
00:33:11,220 --> 00:33:12,977
wouldn't I be able
to work with Mr. He Han

775
00:33:13,044 --> 00:33:14,244
on Shattered Six States?

776
00:33:14,380 --> 00:33:16,410
Who can say what will happen in a month?

777
00:33:16,410 --> 00:33:17,100
No one can say.

778
00:33:17,980 --> 00:33:18,940
No one can say...

779
00:33:18,940 --> 00:33:19,850
Start tomorrow.

780
00:33:19,850 --> 00:33:20,500
We need people.

781
00:33:21,733 --> 00:33:22,540
Sign the contract.

782
00:33:22,700 --> 00:33:23,140
Okay.

783
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,133
Thank you, Mr. He Han.
Thank you, Ms. Lin.

784
00:33:25,260 --> 00:33:26,222
See you tomorrow.

785
00:33:26,740 --> 00:33:27,180
Which way?

786
00:33:27,260 --> 00:33:27,700
Follow me.

787
00:33:33,888 --> 00:33:35,100
She's barely in her twenties.

788
00:33:35,511 --> 00:33:36,666
Don't drag her into this.

789
00:33:36,670 --> 00:33:37,660
What do you mean by "drag?"

790
00:33:37,660 --> 00:33:40,266
I'm helping her. She's my reader.
I should look out for her.

791
00:33:40,380 --> 00:33:41,733
Why did you come to me?

792
00:33:47,100 --> 00:33:47,900
Who is Gu Yan?

793
00:33:49,620 --> 00:33:50,260
You're scared?

794
00:33:52,260 --> 00:33:53,060
So you regret

795
00:33:53,177 --> 00:33:54,666
agreeing to pause for a month?

796
00:33:55,700 --> 00:33:56,620
You can take it back.

797
00:33:57,180 --> 00:33:58,140
No conditions.

798
00:33:59,140 --> 00:34:01,220
You just need to admit
you were arrogant.

799
00:34:02,820 --> 00:34:04,580
He wrote
Journey of a Young Man at the Pass.

800
00:34:05,580 --> 00:34:07,140
The rights belong to Chenxing.

801
00:34:08,100 --> 00:34:09,340
I have the contract you signed.

802
00:34:11,460 --> 00:34:12,820
Dingqi thought the original title

803
00:34:13,088 --> 00:34:14,911
wasn't appealing to female readers,

804
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:16,888
so it was changed to Drunk Old Friend.

805
00:34:18,620 --> 00:34:20,220
Such a good story, and you sold it?

806
00:34:20,466 --> 00:34:21,755
How much did you sell it for?

807
00:34:21,820 --> 00:34:23,533
That's confidential.
I can't disclose it.

808
00:34:23,644 --> 00:34:25,466
Why didn't you develop it yourself?

809
00:34:25,844 --> 00:34:27,288
I didn't have the money.

810
00:34:27,540 --> 00:34:28,220
Satisfied?

811
00:34:32,260 --> 00:34:34,444
So, your last project flopped,

812
00:34:34,488 --> 00:34:35,740
so you lost confidence

813
00:34:35,860 --> 00:34:38,355
and decided to sell this one
and cash out while you could.

814
00:34:38,500 --> 00:34:40,400
That doesn't sound
like you, Lin Zhanqiao.

815
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:42,644
You saw it hit number one
as soon as it launched,

816
00:34:43,780 --> 00:34:44,500
and now you regret

817
00:34:44,500 --> 00:34:46,140
not continuing
the story yourself, right?

818
00:34:46,733 --> 00:34:48,460
I thought the story
had problems back then,

819
00:34:48,460 --> 00:34:49,980
and I still think it does.

820
00:34:50,380 --> 00:34:51,460
But you have to admit,

821
00:34:51,980 --> 00:34:54,260
Gu Yan wrote those first 20 chapters

822
00:34:54,500 --> 00:34:55,420
better than you.

823
00:34:57,044 --> 00:34:58,311
I didn't even write them.

824
00:34:58,377 --> 00:35:00,066
How do you know he's better than I am?

825
00:35:00,180 --> 00:35:01,100
Because you're scared.

826
00:35:02,977 --> 00:35:05,111
Otherwise, you wouldn't
come asking me who he is.

827
00:35:06,020 --> 00:35:07,380
You've never cared

828
00:35:07,380 --> 00:35:09,620
about someone writing
a story you once rejected.

829
00:35:10,060 --> 00:35:10,860
If this were before,

830
00:35:11,540 --> 00:35:12,700
you wouldn't even bother.

831
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:20,620
I'm worried about you.

832
00:35:22,100 --> 00:35:22,980
You lost Hong Qigong,

833
00:35:23,244 --> 00:35:25,977
and now you've brought out
a Gu Yan from Dingqi Platform.

834
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:28,266
What cards do you have left to play?

835
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:30,777
Online fiction writers

836
00:35:30,860 --> 00:35:32,555
turn over every five to seven years.

837
00:35:32,980 --> 00:35:33,820
Editors stay,

838
00:35:34,020 --> 00:35:35,222
and authors come and go.

839
00:35:35,622 --> 00:35:37,511
I'm an editor. I can afford to wait.

840
00:35:37,820 --> 00:35:38,500
You can't.

841
00:35:39,740 --> 00:35:40,900
You've held the top spot

842
00:35:40,900 --> 00:35:42,222
for five or six years already.

843
00:35:42,260 --> 00:35:43,460
You'll be replaced soon enough.

844
00:35:47,900 --> 00:35:49,420
Take care, Lin Zhanqiao.

845
00:35:54,620 --> 00:35:55,500
Are you free tonight?

846
00:35:56,180 --> 00:35:57,420
- Love-Obsessed Husband made No. 3.
- Mei,

847
00:35:57,420 --> 00:35:58,820
- Come by my place after work?
- Let's celebrate.

848
00:35:59,100 --> 00:35:59,820
- Want to join us?
- Yeah.

849
00:35:59,820 --> 00:36:00,700
- Seven tonight.
- Just message me.

850
00:36:00,700 --> 00:36:01,490
I'll send you the address.

851
00:36:01,500 --> 00:36:01,900
Okay.

852
00:36:02,460 --> 00:36:02,820
Yeah.

853
00:36:14,540 --> 00:36:14,900
Hello?

854
00:36:17,460 --> 00:36:17,780
Mei,

855
00:36:18,688 --> 00:36:20,155
are you free after work tonight

856
00:36:20,177 --> 00:36:21,377
to come by my place?

857
00:36:21,444 --> 00:36:23,488
I've got an appointment
with Lawyer Bei tonight.

858
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:24,800
I'll be back pretty late.

859
00:36:25,780 --> 00:36:27,580
Can't you just give
your mom your door code?

860
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:30,620
She's been waiting in
the hallway every time.

861
00:36:30,666 --> 00:36:33,000
If the neighbors see,
they'll think you're neglecting her.

862
00:36:33,044 --> 00:36:34,210
But it's my home.

863
00:36:34,210 --> 00:36:35,660
I can't just give her the code.

864
00:36:36,860 --> 00:36:38,100
I've already told her clearly

865
00:36:38,100 --> 00:36:38,940
that no one's home

866
00:36:38,940 --> 00:36:40,540
and not to come over.

867
00:36:40,980 --> 00:36:42,460
But I can't stop her.

868
00:36:44,300 --> 00:36:45,260
She may be my mother,

869
00:36:45,666 --> 00:36:47,377
but there are boundaries
between us.

870
00:37:14,220 --> 00:37:14,660
Thank you.

871
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:22,733
You don't drink?

872
00:37:23,444 --> 00:37:25,000
We don't drink when talking about work.

873
00:37:25,822 --> 00:37:27,488
Your wife doesn't let you drink?

874
00:37:29,220 --> 00:37:31,200
Being overly aggressive
isn't a good habit.

875
00:37:33,060 --> 00:37:35,260
Rules have to be set
when it's time to set them.

876
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:39,740
So,

877
00:37:41,060 --> 00:37:43,540
are you really taking this to court?

878
00:37:44,140 --> 00:37:44,460
Yes.

879
00:37:45,444 --> 00:37:46,711
I want them to compensate me

880
00:37:46,844 --> 00:37:47,940
and publicly apologize.

881
00:37:48,580 --> 00:37:49,660
But if you do that,

882
00:37:50,380 --> 00:37:51,940
won't everything become public?

883
00:37:52,780 --> 00:37:53,540
Aren't you worried

884
00:37:53,940 --> 00:37:55,340
about people gossiping?

885
00:37:56,180 --> 00:37:56,860
Not at all.

886
00:37:57,511 --> 00:37:59,800
It's not the first time people
have talked about me.

887
00:37:59,977 --> 00:38:01,740
Might as well let everyone
in the company see

888
00:38:02,060 --> 00:38:03,955
what happens
when they bully and defame me.

889
00:38:06,740 --> 00:38:07,180
Alright.

890
00:38:08,460 --> 00:38:09,260
In that case,

891
00:38:09,900 --> 00:38:10,580
I'll make sure

892
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:12,020
this gets maximum exposure.

893
00:38:12,260 --> 00:38:12,580
Good.

894
00:38:15,860 --> 00:38:16,460
Then,

895
00:38:17,060 --> 00:38:18,300
since work is done,

896
00:38:19,022 --> 00:38:19,822
let's have a drink.

897
00:38:21,020 --> 00:38:21,420
Just one.

898
00:38:22,740 --> 00:38:23,180
Excuse me,

899
00:38:23,444 --> 00:38:24,355
liquor list, please.

900
00:38:39,700 --> 00:38:41,460
Your cholesterol is high.
Have some greens.

901
00:38:41,580 --> 00:38:41,900
Here.

902
00:38:55,555 --> 00:38:56,460
You order first.

903
00:38:56,980 --> 00:38:58,111
I'll go to the restroom.

904
00:39:26,700 --> 00:39:27,340
Didn't you say

905
00:39:27,340 --> 00:39:28,620
you wouldn't see her again?

906
00:39:33,466 --> 00:39:35,660
We just happened to run
into each other at a lecture.

907
00:39:35,660 --> 00:39:36,890
What's wrong with
having a meal together?

908
00:39:36,890 --> 00:39:37,580
A lecture?

909
00:39:38,177 --> 00:39:39,933
You think she understands any of that?

910
00:39:40,420 --> 00:39:42,020
All she cares about is houses and cars.

911
00:39:42,260 --> 00:39:43,940
You're being way too controlling.

912
00:39:45,222 --> 00:39:47,288
What's wrong with
wanting a house and a car?

913
00:39:47,290 --> 00:39:47,900
Is it illegal?

914
00:39:47,900 --> 00:39:48,740
No.

915
00:39:49,340 --> 00:39:51,260
But wanting mine is not acceptable.

916
00:39:52,140 --> 00:39:53,140
We're genuinely in love.

917
00:39:53,380 --> 00:39:54,466
Please show some mercy.

918
00:39:55,580 --> 00:39:57,420
You're "in love" when he has money,

919
00:39:57,577 --> 00:39:59,540
and when he doesn't,
it's "fate has ended."

920
00:39:59,688 --> 00:40:01,660
Even sex workers
have more dignity than you.

921
00:40:01,660 --> 00:40:02,260
Zhou!

922
00:40:24,220 --> 00:40:25,420
That was too far.

923
00:40:32,940 --> 00:40:34,100
Zhou Mei, listen carefully.

924
00:40:35,140 --> 00:40:36,660
You only get to say that once.

925
00:40:40,088 --> 00:40:40,977
What are you doing?

926
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:41,533
You...

927
00:40:42,060 --> 00:40:42,540
Zhou,

928
00:40:43,980 --> 00:40:44,500
are you okay?

929
00:40:47,380 --> 00:40:47,780
I'm fine.

930
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:48,780
Who is he?

931
00:40:50,220 --> 00:40:50,980
Your new boyfriend

932
00:40:52,020 --> 00:40:52,660
or your boss?

933
00:40:53,300 --> 00:40:54,300
He's my lawyer.

934
00:40:55,780 --> 00:40:57,060
So you'd better watch yourself.

935
00:40:57,980 --> 00:40:58,580
You, too.

936
00:41:25,660 --> 00:41:28,620
♪My heart is beating still♪

937
00:41:29,740 --> 00:41:32,660
♪Sometimes I feel alone♪

938
00:41:33,420 --> 00:41:36,500
♪But love should not be frail♪

939
00:41:38,700 --> 00:41:39,380
Just now,

940
00:41:39,977 --> 00:41:41,755
why didn't you let me call the police?

941
00:41:44,700 --> 00:41:45,466
He's my father.

942
00:41:48,900 --> 00:41:50,288
Every bit of money my dad makes

943
00:41:51,220 --> 00:41:52,380
gets taken by women.

944
00:41:53,780 --> 00:41:54,466
You know that?

945
00:41:55,355 --> 00:41:56,500
I have two younger brothers.

946
00:41:57,740 --> 00:41:58,980
The three of us

947
00:42:00,140 --> 00:42:01,700
have different mothers.

948
00:42:02,220 --> 00:42:02,980
♪I guess♪

949
00:42:02,980 --> 00:42:08,220
♪It's rising from my silence♪

950
00:42:09,820 --> 00:42:12,300
♪I'm nothing but the one♪

951
00:42:12,300 --> 00:42:15,200
Make sure you protect your share
of the assets and your mother's.

952
00:42:15,620 --> 00:42:16,420
If necessary,

953
00:42:17,100 --> 00:42:18,700
I can help you get everything notarized.

954
00:42:19,100 --> 00:42:20,740
♪And past pain♪

955
00:42:20,900 --> 00:42:22,540
♪I'd still try♪

956
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:24,377
You'll probably laugh
at me for saying this,

957
00:42:25,660 --> 00:42:26,620
but my mom, even now,

958
00:42:26,980 --> 00:42:28,420
is still waiting for him to change.

959
00:42:28,420 --> 00:42:29,660
♪Please stay with me♪

960
00:42:30,340 --> 00:42:33,780
♪I could've held you in my arms♪

961
00:42:34,340 --> 00:42:36,580
♪When I said love♪

962
00:42:36,580 --> 00:42:39,580
♪Hurts somehow♪

963
00:42:41,380 --> 00:42:44,980
♪Please stand by me♪

964
00:42:45,780 --> 00:42:46,220
Waitress,

965
00:42:46,511 --> 00:42:47,420
two more drinks.

966
00:42:48,100 --> 00:42:48,500
Alright.

967
00:42:52,380 --> 00:42:53,540
Didn't you say just one?

968
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:56,400
I'm drinking with you tonight.

969
00:43:05,220 --> 00:43:06,700
The company hasn't seen
any contract with him.

970
00:43:07,020 --> 00:43:08,300
I registered a brand-new one.

971
00:43:08,940 --> 00:43:09,620
To guard against us?

972
00:43:10,060 --> 00:43:11,220
It's him I'm guarding against, not you.

973
00:43:12,100 --> 00:43:12,820
A female partner?

974
00:43:14,180 --> 00:43:14,820
I don't agree.

975
00:43:15,460 --> 00:43:16,780
When you can bring in
ten million in investment,

976
00:43:17,620 --> 00:43:18,940
then you can disagree.

977
00:43:19,780 --> 00:43:20,900
Congratulations, Ms. Lin.

978
00:43:20,900 --> 00:43:22,500
(Chapter 63: Music and Dance Mystery)
That was quite a deceptive move.

979
00:43:22,500 --> 00:43:23,620
But I'm busy right now,

980
00:43:24,780 --> 00:43:26,540
Why are you bringing up a breakup

981
00:43:26,540 --> 00:43:27,860
when I'm at my absolute best?

982
00:43:28,020 --> 00:43:30,260
Wouldn't it be even scummier
to leave when you're down?

983
00:43:34,140 --> 00:43:35,180
He Han still loves you.

984
00:43:39,080 --> 00:43:40,200
(I've been thinking.)

985
00:43:41,480 --> 00:43:44,760
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

986
00:43:45,520 --> 00:43:52,850
(is probably different.)

987
00:43:53,850 --> 00:43:55,600
♪If the sky♪

988
00:43:56,110 --> 00:43:57,510
♪And the sea♪

989
00:43:58,050 --> 00:43:59,760
♪Turned upside down♪

990
00:44:01,320 --> 00:44:03,250
♪If a swimming fish♪

991
00:44:03,650 --> 00:44:07,040
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

992
00:44:08,810 --> 00:44:10,780
♪If back then♪

993
00:44:11,140 --> 00:44:15,550
♪We had never let go♪

994
00:44:16,150 --> 00:44:22,430
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

995
00:44:23,550 --> 00:44:25,700
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

996
00:44:25,700 --> 00:44:27,570
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

997
00:44:27,750 --> 00:44:30,190
♪And found our way back whole♪

998
00:44:31,030 --> 00:44:33,200
♪So let this surging love♪

999
00:44:33,200 --> 00:44:37,630
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

1000
00:44:38,530 --> 00:44:40,710
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

1001
00:44:40,710 --> 00:44:41,800
♪That's alright♪

1002
00:44:42,340 --> 00:44:43,090
♪If we're buried♪

1003
00:44:43,090 --> 00:44:45,790
♪By passing years all the better♪

1004
00:44:46,050 --> 00:44:48,230
♪At least we still can keep♪

1005
00:44:48,410 --> 00:44:52,830
♪This one eternal photograph♪

1006
00:45:08,590 --> 00:45:10,880
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

1007
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:12,640
♪Running in opposite ways♪

1008
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:15,230
♪Searching all along the way♪

1009
00:45:16,030 --> 00:45:18,190
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

1010
00:45:18,380 --> 00:45:23,290
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

1011
00:45:23,290 --> 00:45:26,810
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

1012
00:45:27,050 --> 00:45:28,020
♪Only after loss♪

1013
00:45:28,020 --> 00:45:30,650
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

1014
00:45:31,060 --> 00:45:33,420
♪In another time and space♪

1015
00:45:33,420 --> 00:45:34,980
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

1016
00:45:34,980 --> 00:45:37,810
♪Till we grow old♪

1017
00:45:38,770 --> 00:45:41,060
♪But still the sky will never♪

1018
00:45:41,060 --> 00:45:43,730
♪Turn with the sea♪

1019
00:45:46,250 --> 00:45:48,660
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

1020
00:45:48,660 --> 00:45:53,870
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
